1
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:55,120
Mr. Peeraka Jaiaree.

2
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:58,000
<i>The area is surrounded.</i>

3
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:05,120
I trusted you.

4
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:07,280
But in the end…

5
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:11,160
It feels like I'm the one who killed Raka.

6
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:13,680
You're such a beautiful
and generous girlfriend.

7
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:15,800
Mr. Mahasamut is very lucky.

8
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,440
- Right?
- Yeah.

9
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:26,000
If someone once devoted themselves to you,

10
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,280
you should've taken better care of them.

11
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:29,480
All you have to do

12
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:32,880
is plug this into the main computer
in the control room.

13
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,440
Here we go.

14
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:43,080
Great. From now on,
I will control everything from here.

15
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:46,120
Let's begin with…

16
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:56,120
What's wrong?

17
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:59,320
Are you cold? Or scared of ghosts?

18
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,480
Or are you scared of me?

19
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,760
Don't tell me you followed me.

20
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:10,320
Women these days are really confident.

21
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:13,640
This is a hotel.

22
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:16,279
I can meet whoever I want,
though I do have standards.

23
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:18,680
You started it,

24
00:04:19,279 --> 00:04:21,000
accusing me of following you.

25
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:41,280
It'll start working again soon.

26
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:49,720
Yes?

27
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:51,640
The elevator is stuck. Can you hear me?

28
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:54,480
We're fixing it right now, ma'am.

29
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:57,520
We're aware of it.

30
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:59,040
Thank you.

31
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:00,800
Yes, ma'am.

32
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:04,280
Never been stuck in an elevator before?

33
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:10,040
I get stuck all the time.

34
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:13,080
The taller the building,
the higher the chance.

35
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:15,840
The longest I've been stuck
was about two hours.

36
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:19,000
At first you panic,

37
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:20,720
wondering

38
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:24,040
if you'll have enough air
or if it'll crash to the ground.

39
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,480
Hey.

40
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:27,200
Can you stop talking?

41
00:05:29,320 --> 00:05:30,160
Scared?

42
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:34,440
- Are you scared of dying?
- Hey!

43
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:38,400
Death is normal. Everyone dies eventually.

44
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:49,560
She took out her phone.

45
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:51,520
There's no signal in here.

46
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:54,280
Try it.

47
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:06,520
Phone unlocked.

48
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:09,840
I've got this.

49
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:22,440
Hey.

50
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:25,440
Hey.

51
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,680
Calm down.

52
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:30,440
Calm down.

53
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:36,440
Get me out, please.

54
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:37,680
Breathe slowly.

55
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:41,400
Hey.

56
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,680
Breathe slowly.

57
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:49,120
Don't be scared.

58
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:53,280
We'll get out of here together.

59
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:56,080
You'll be safe.

60
00:06:59,080 --> 00:07:00,320
Trust me.

61
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:09,760
Don't be scared.

62
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:12,960
We'll get out of here.

63
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,520
Trust me.

64
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:32,360
You…

65
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:38,960
- Dad.
- You're awake.

66
00:08:40,559 --> 00:08:41,679
How are you?

67
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:43,720
You must've been really scared.

68
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:47,600
It was just an elevator malfunction.

69
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:49,000
I already had it checked.

70
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:54,160
I fainted?

71
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:59,400
I thought I was getting better.

72
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,320
Oh.

73
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:18,320
Tomorrow is the foundation opening.

74
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:24,320
<i>Can you go?</i>

75
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:27,200
<i>Yong said everything is ready.</i>

76
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,480
<i>Yes.</i>

77
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:40,760
<i>I'm fine now.</i>

78
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:44,080
<i>That's good.</i>

79
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:52,360
Crystal clear.

80
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:55,600
Every pore is visible.

81
00:10:44,040 --> 00:10:45,920
Tracking software is installed.

82
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:49,920
Now we can access everything
on Ms. Fahsai's phone,

83
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:53,320
camera, mic, GPS.

84
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:57,760
Honestly, we can access
pretty much everything.

85
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:07,960
<i>A female politician starting a foundation</i>
<i>for women is the best image possible.</i>

86
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:10,960
<i>We need to start now and build the base.</i>

87
00:11:11,560 --> 00:11:16,440
By the time you run for office,
people will trust you.

88
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,240
This kid!

89
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:17,480
Why aren't you helping?

90
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:19,200
Oh, Peekul, don't hit your brother.

91
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:21,280
- Here, have some drinks and snacks first.
- Mom, he only plays games.

92
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:22,480
Have some drinks and snacks.

93
00:12:22,560 --> 00:12:24,680
Drink first.

94
00:12:24,760 --> 00:12:25,920
- Hey, hey. Split up.
- No.

95
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,000
It's dead.

96
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:28,880
Serves you right!

97
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:30,760
Alright, alright, drink first.

98
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:31,680
- That's enough.
- No!

99
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:33,600
- Hey, hey. Mom.
- What?

100
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:35,760
Mom.

101
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:17,680
Fahsai Foundation?

102
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:22,680
After doing something that vile…

103
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:26,960
They have a nerve.

104
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:36,960
Help…

105
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:20,880
Welcome back to the world.

106
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:24,240
Or maybe just another circle of hell.

107
00:14:25,880 --> 00:14:27,480
I told you before.

108
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:31,960
I'd repay you. A life for a life.

109
00:14:35,280 --> 00:14:36,920
Now we're even.

110
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:42,720
What a pity.

111
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:46,240
You should've had better luck.

112
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:48,600
But that's how it is, isn't it?

113
00:14:49,640 --> 00:14:51,520
People make mistakes
with those closest to them.

114
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,280
Do you remember my son Wayu?

115
00:15:20,360 --> 00:15:21,520
He's dead.

116
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:37,960
Why?

117
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:42,360
Why did it end like this?

118
00:15:43,520 --> 00:15:45,040
I'm sorry I survived, boss.

119
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:49,080
Because they thought I was dead.

120
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:50,080
Hey!

121
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:53,480
Don't you know who my father is?

122
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:57,960
Then do you know who my boss is?

123
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:02,560
He'd even dare go after your father.

124
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,360
As for me,

125
00:16:04,920 --> 00:16:05,800
I'm just borrowing

126
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,520
his power to avenge Leng.

127
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:15,920
Be glad.

128
00:16:17,400 --> 00:16:20,320
This is your illegal gun.

129
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:26,320
Why…

130
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:36,920
Why, my son?

131
00:16:54,920 --> 00:16:56,280
‪I'm sorry for your loss.

132
00:16:56,920 --> 00:17:01,320
My son died following in my footsteps.

133
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:05,680
And I can't let the people who killed him

134
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:09,160
become powerful and get away with it.

135
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:19,839
I'm going to make you my son.

136
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,400
Not just my adopted son,

137
00:17:26,040 --> 00:17:28,400
but Wayu Buranachat.

138
00:17:34,080 --> 00:17:36,680
MRS. VIPA JAIAREE
MS. PEEKUL JAIAREE

139
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:40,760
The people who killed your family

140
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:43,040
are powerful politicians.

141
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:45,000
They have far more power

142
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,720
than you.

143
00:17:50,080 --> 00:17:52,240
If you tell the truth,
do you think you'll survive?

144
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:55,400
If they don't kill you,

145
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:59,680
you'll still be prosecuted
for murdering your mother and sister.

146
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:01,480
It can't be like this…

147
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:08,560
‪Mom.

148
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:10,520
Can you come back?

149
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:14,800
Can you wake up?

150
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:30,960
I'll become Wayu Buranachat

151
00:18:31,960 --> 00:18:33,080
for one reason only.

152
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:38,560
They're going to learn
what hell feels like.

153
00:18:39,760 --> 00:18:41,440
The same hell they gave everyone else.

154
00:19:34,120 --> 00:19:35,240
From now on,

155
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:38,640
there will be no more Peeraka Jaiaree.

156
00:19:40,040 --> 00:19:41,920
There will only be Wayu

157
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:44,000
Buranachat.

158
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:57,960
<i>Hello, people of Thailand.</i>

159
00:19:58,960 --> 00:20:00,560
Wow, I've been waiting for this.

160
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:03,520
- Hey, look.
- Hm?

161
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:05,560
Pitbull is on himself.

162
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:07,600
This has to be big.

163
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:10,120
<i>Tonight, I've got a surprise for you.</i>

164
00:20:11,360 --> 00:20:12,760
<i>Don't blink.</i>

165
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:22,560
<i>Well? Did you see that?</i>

166
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:25,560
<i>I know some of you</i>

167
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:28,360
<i>investigate almost as well</i>
<i>as the Mad Dog Gang.</i>

168
00:20:30,640 --> 00:20:33,120
<i>This place is a charitable foundation</i>

169
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:35,000
<i>run by the daughter of a certain minister,</i>

170
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:39,160
<i>with a grand opening tomorrow.</i>

171
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:43,320
<i>But what dark secret</i>
<i>is really hidden there?</i>

172
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:47,160
<i>We're going to rip off the mask</i>
<i>and expose the truth live</i>

173
00:20:47,680 --> 00:20:51,080
<i>on the Mad Dog News page</i>

174
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:52,560
<i>tomorrow.</i>

175
00:20:53,080 --> 00:20:55,840
<i>We'll howl it out for you ourselves.</i>

176
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:30,840
Thank you so much for agreeing to come
to the opening of our Fahsai Foundation.

177
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:34,120
It's okay. I can come.

178
00:21:36,080 --> 00:21:37,800
The reporters will ask questions.

179
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:40,000
I already screened them for you.

180
00:21:43,760 --> 00:21:46,960
Yong, are the girls' masks
and glasses ready?

181
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:50,760
Yong? Yong?

182
00:21:50,840 --> 00:21:52,240
Huh? Yes? What is it?

183
00:21:52,320 --> 00:21:53,920
The girls' masks and glasses.

184
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,920
Masks and glasses… Oh. Okay.

185
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,320
Yes, everything's ready.

186
00:21:57,400 --> 00:21:59,120
What are you spacing out about?

187
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:02,440
Nothing.

188
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:09,160
The event starts at one,
so we still have time.

189
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:11,400
Why don't we stop for lunch first?

190
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:13,360
What do you girls want to eat?

191
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:15,000
Oh, <i>Kon La Yum</i>.

192
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:18,880
Oh, so this is where it is.

193
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:22,560
This place gets tons of reviews.
Everyone says it's really good.

194
00:22:23,120 --> 00:22:25,200
Then should we eat here?

195
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:28,640
Okay then, let's eat.

196
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:31,120
Let's eat, girls.

197
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:37,760
- Where should we sit?
- Welcome.

198
00:22:38,760 --> 00:22:41,920
Let's find a table first.

199
00:22:43,240 --> 00:22:44,120
Hey!

200
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:46,600
I'm eating in this life,

201
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:48,160
not the next one.

202
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:49,640
It's in order, sir.

203
00:22:51,120 --> 00:22:53,320
It hasn't even been ten minutes
since you ordered.

204
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:56,080
But I keep seeing you
serving other tables.

205
00:22:57,840 --> 00:22:59,960
They came before you.

206
00:23:02,080 --> 00:23:03,480
Then I'm not waiting anymore.

207
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:07,440
Everything on this table
counts as compensation.

208
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:08,520
Let's go.

209
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:16,880
Hey!

210
00:23:28,080 --> 00:23:31,200
Since you're really hungry,
I'll serve you myself.

211
00:23:38,560 --> 00:23:39,600
Do you know

212
00:23:41,120 --> 00:23:42,280
what's the most expensive thing?

213
00:23:43,040 --> 00:23:43,960
I know you wouldn't dare.

214
00:23:44,040 --> 00:23:46,280
Otherwise, I'll film this,
expose your restaurant,

215
00:23:46,360 --> 00:23:48,440
and ruin you online.

216
00:23:48,520 --> 00:23:49,360
Record it.

217
00:23:49,440 --> 00:23:50,320
No need.

218
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:55,040
I already filmed everything
from the beginning.

219
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:57,120
Post it,

220
00:23:57,200 --> 00:24:01,000
and let's see how many times
you've pulled this trick to eat for free.

221
00:24:01,080 --> 00:24:03,360
The vendors around here
will blacklist you for sure.

222
00:24:05,160 --> 00:24:06,080
Pay them.

223
00:24:16,520 --> 00:24:17,960
You overpaid by 102 baht, bro.

224
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:20,760
Yeah.

225
00:24:20,840 --> 00:24:22,280
<i>Oppa!</i>

226
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:23,720
That's how it should be.

227
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:27,040
- <i>Saranghae.</i>
- Thank you, everyone.

228
00:24:27,120 --> 00:24:31,000
Please enjoy your meal.
And your food will be served in order.

229
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:39,760
Here you go. Seafood Mass Murder.

230
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:43,000
And Salmon Bathed in Blood.

231
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:46,600
And Exploding Jungle Som Tam.

232
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:49,480
Let it explode!

233
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:52,840
And this one's on the house for the kids.

234
00:24:52,920 --> 00:24:53,920
That's everything.

235
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:56,080
Alright, girls, let's eat.

236
00:24:56,160 --> 00:24:57,880
Go ahead and enjoy your food.

237
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:07,840
Ms. Fahsai.

238
00:25:19,280 --> 00:25:21,280
The chairwoman has to start first, right?

239
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:40,040
It's really good. Eat it.

240
00:25:40,120 --> 00:25:41,720
Is it spicy?

241
00:25:57,600 --> 00:26:00,200
Do politicians all love
putting on an act like this?

242
00:26:03,440 --> 00:26:05,160
Here, fresh milk.

243
00:26:06,160 --> 00:26:07,880
Best way to kill the heat fast.

244
00:26:08,640 --> 00:26:09,520
No need.

245
00:26:16,040 --> 00:26:17,720
I've seen plenty of people like you.

246
00:26:18,280 --> 00:26:19,400
Act tough about spicy food.

247
00:26:31,720 --> 00:26:33,440
Why make yourself suffer?

248
00:26:34,640 --> 00:26:36,120
Or do you enjoy pain?

249
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:54,000
Hey, slow down, or you'll choke.

250
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:11,840
Hey, wait.

251
00:27:24,360 --> 00:27:25,800
With the way you're acting,

252
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:29,160
you're not about to accuse me
of following you again, are you?

253
00:27:31,040 --> 00:27:33,120
You're going to tell me
it's just another coincidence?

254
00:27:33,760 --> 00:27:34,840
No.

255
00:27:39,240 --> 00:27:40,680
I own this place.

256
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:43,400
You're the one who came in here.

257
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:03,280
So now I'm confused, boss.

258
00:28:03,360 --> 00:28:06,240
Didn't you say
you hated that whole family?

259
00:28:08,200 --> 00:28:09,560
Its because I hate her

260
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:12,120
that I can't let her die yet.

261
00:28:18,680 --> 00:28:20,160
Here.

262
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,440
What?

263
00:28:22,160 --> 00:28:23,760
- You want me to drink it?
- Wash it.

264
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:49,920
Sir, may we take a few photos?

265
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:52,880
- Hello, everyone.
- Please.

266
00:28:52,960 --> 00:28:54,560
- This camera, please.
- This too, please.

267
00:28:54,640 --> 00:28:57,600
- See you inside.
- Yes, sir.

268
00:28:57,680 --> 00:28:58,720
Yes.

269
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:04,280
- May we take a few photos?
- Please stay close to each other.

270
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:06,720
This way, please.

271
00:29:06,800 --> 00:29:09,280
- One, two, three.
- This way too, please.

272
00:29:09,360 --> 00:29:10,560
Please smile.

273
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:13,320
